records.addlTxt:
3:15 PM Defendant Forest F Molski in court.  Attorney David R. Knaapen in court for State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Blake Duren in court for Forest F Molski. 
Investigator Sergeant Pleet is sworn in and testifies. Testifies to being an Investigator with the Wood County Sheriff's Department. Testifies to specializing with the Wisconsin Drug Force Task. Testifies to being dispatched to a residence for a report of a possible drug over dose. Testifies to finding the subject BAB at that location. Testifies to BAB being on the gurney already when he arrived. Testifies to BAB going to the hospital and the state BAB was in. Testifies to conducting an interview with BAB. Testifies to a statement made by BAB. Testifies to going to the Econo lodge and conducting a search warrant on the room the defendant was staying in. Witness identifies the defendant in court, court recognizes. Attorney Duren objects to identification and makes an argument regarding identification of the defendant w/ the statement from BAB. Witness testifies to not remembering if BAB gave the defendants last name or not. Testifies to the initial call being a suspected over dose call. 
Attorney Duren addresses his objection again regarding identification.
Court finds probable cause to believe a felony was committed and the defendant committed it.

Bond is continued.
Attorney Duren is requesting his other case gets a new sentencing date due to the defendant having back surgery.
Final pre-trial scheduled for November 10, 2022 at 03:00 pm.
